{"word":"H4322 - מִיכָיָהוּ - Mîykâyâhûw - me-kaw-yaw'-hoo - Michaiah","slug":"H4322","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">מִיכָיָהוּ</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>Mîykâyâhûw"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>me-kaw-yaw'-hoo"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Michaiah"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"Original: <b><he>מיכיהוּ</he></b> <p />Transliteration: <b>mı̂ykâyâhû</b> <p />Phonetic: <b>me-kaw-yaw'-hoo</b> <p class=\"bdb_def\"><b>BDB Definition</b>:</p> Michaiah = \"who is like God\" <ol><li>one of the princes of Jehoshaphat whom he sent to teach the law of Jehovah in the cities of Judah</li><li>daughter of Uriel of Gibeah, wife of king Rehoboam of Judah, and mother of king Abijah of Judah</li></ol> <p />Origin: for <a href=\"#/H4320\">H4320</a> <p />TWOT entry: None <p />Part(s) of speech: "},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H4310\">H4310</a>, <a href=\"#/H4311\">H4311</a>, <a href=\"#/H4316\">H4316</a>, <a href=\"#/H4317\">H4317</a>, <a href=\"#/H4318\">H4318</a>, <a href=\"#/H4319\">H4319</a>, <a href=\"#/H4320\">H4320</a>, <a href=\"#/H4321\">H4321</a>, <a href=\"#/H4323\">H4323</a>, <a href=\"#/H4324\">H4324</a>, <a href=\"#/H4326\">H4326</a>, <a href=\"#/H4332\">H4332</a>, <a href=\"#/H4509\">H4509</a>"}]}